<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_029760"><name>1VD-FTV ENGINE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0135360"><name>ECD SYSTEM</name><para id="RM100000000FJJG" category="C"><dtccode>P0500</dtccode><dtcname>Vehicle Speed Sensor &quot;A&quot;</dtcname><subpara id="RM100000000FJJG_01" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The speed sensor detects the wheel speed and sends the appropriate signals to the skid control ECU. The skid control ECU converts these wheel speed signals into a 4-pulse signal and outputs it to the ECM via the combination meter. The ECM determines the vehicle speed based on the frequency of these pulse signals.</ptxt><figure translate="E" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A115899E35" height="2.799876969in" width="7.168479331in"/></figure><table type="dtc-explan-table" pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="6"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.42in"/><colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.70in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Detection Item</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>MIL</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Memory</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0500</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Vehicle Speed Sensor &quot;A&quot;</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>When one of the following conditions is met:</ptxt><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Following conditions (a), (b), (c) and (d) met for 8 seconds or more:</ptxt><ptxt>(2 trip detection logic)</ptxt></item><list2 type="ordered"><item><ptxt>Engine coolant temperature more than 70°C (158°F)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Engine speed between 1500 rpm and 4000 rpm</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Vehicle running</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No speed signal input to ECM</ptxt></item></list2><item><ptxt>Following conditions (a), (b) and (c) met for 5 seconds or more:</ptxt></item><list2 type="ordered"><item><ptxt>Vehicle running</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Under fuel-cut operation</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No speed signal is input to ECM</ptxt></item></list2></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in speed signal circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Brake actuator assembly</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Combination meter</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJJG_06" category="03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="A276508E03" width="7.168479331in" height="3.812598425in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJJG_07" category="10"><name>CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT</name><content5><atten3><ptxt>After replacing the ECM, the new ECM needs registration (See page <mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJKB"/></mlink>) and initialization (See page <mlink><xref label="Seep00002" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJIX"/></mlink>).</ptxt></atten3><atten4><ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the GTS. Freeze frame data records the engine condition when malfunctions are detected. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can help determine if the vehicle was moving or stationary, if the engine was warmed up or not, and other data from the time the malfunction occurred.</ptxt></atten4></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJJG_09" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM100000000FJJG_09_0001" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>CHECK OPERATION OF SPEEDOMETER</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Drive the vehicle and check whether the operation of the speedometer in the combination meter is normal.</ptxt><atten4><ptxt>The vehicle speed sensor is operating normally if the speedometer reading is normal.</ptxt></atten4><spec type="other"><title>OK</title><specitem><ptxt>The vehicle speed sensor is operating normally.</ptxt></specitem></spec><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="1-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-1" childid="RM100000000FJJG_09_0003"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="1-3"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="2-3"><actiontitle>GO TO SPEEDOMETER MALFUNCTION</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" term-id-to="002" href="RM100000000FSUS"/><xref term-id-from="002" href="RM10000000101PZ"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000FJJG_09_0003" cellposition="2-1"><testtitle>READ VALUE USING GTS (VEHICLE SPEED)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Connect the GTS to the DLC3.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch ON and start the engine.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the GTS ON.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Enter the following menus: Powertrain / Engine and ECT / Data List / All Data / Vehicle Speed.</ptxt><gts-info category="data-list"><title>Powertrain &gt; Engine and ECT &gt; Data List</title><table type="data-list"><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Display</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="item-name" args1="316"><ptxt>Vehicle Speed</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><gts-exec function-id="50003"><gts-ecu ecu-id="61"><gts-pid pid-id="316"/></gts-ecu></gts-exec><app-communication><app-param name="process-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="edit-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="insert-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="function-tab">2</app-param><app-param name="category-div">1</app-param><app-param name="category-div-name">Powertrain</app-param><app-param name="ecu-id">61</app-param><app-param name="ecu-name">Engine and ECT</app-param><app-param name="gts-order">0</app-param><app-param-unit><app-param name="pid-id">316</app-param><app-param name="data-list-item-name">Vehicle Speed</app-param><app-param name="exception-process-id"/><app-param name="exception-process-div"/></app-param-unit></app-communication></gts-info></test1><test1><ptxt>Drive the vehicle.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Read the value displayed on the GTS.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>OK</title><specitem><ptxt>Vehicle speeds displayed on tester and speedometer display are equal.NG</ptxt></specitem></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="2-1"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-1"><actiontitle>CHECK FOR INTERMITTENT PROBLEMS</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJK6"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="2-2"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="3-2" childid="RM100000000FJJG_09_0012"/></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000FJJG_09_0012" cellposition="3-2"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (COMBINATION METER ASSEMBLY - ECM)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the L25 combination meter connector.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the A29 ECM connector.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard resistance</title><table><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>L25-8 (+S) - A29-8 (SPD)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>L25-8 (+S) or A29-8 (SPD) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="3-2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="4-2"><actiontitle>GO TO SPEED SENSOR CIRCUIT</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" term-id-to="002" href="RM100000000FSUX"/><xref term-id-from="002" href="RM10000000101QT"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="3-3"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="4-3"><actiontitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE HARNESS OR CONNECTOR</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp></subpara></para></ttl></section></servcat></pub></tmc-service-paragraph>